#Istarted off uninstalling all my OpenSSH so that i will struggle the whole way
first verify uou have Open SSH 
Get-WindowsCapability -Online | Where-Object Name -like 'OpenSSH*'

Then lets install OpenSHH, if bot the cliet and server are intalled skip this part. 
# Install the OpenSSH Client
Add-WindowsCapability -Online -Name OpenSSH.Client~~~~0.0.1.0
Restart required
# Install the OpenSSH Server
# Install the OpenSSH Client
Add-WindowsCapability -Online -Name OpenSSH.Client~~~~0.0.1.0

# Install the OpenSSH Server
Add-WindowsCapability -Online -Name OpenSSH.Server~~~~0.0.1.0
Here you may get and error if so we gonna install it via GUI
